cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.RO, cs.AI 

The paper discusses efficient normal integration methods for computer vision tasks such as shape-from-shading, photometric stereo, and deflectometry, which are all related to computer vision and graphics (cs.CV, cs.GR). The paper also mentions the need for fast and robust methods, which are important in multimedia processing (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of variational methods, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
